title: Corporate Events Support
overview: The meeting discusses corporate events support, product announcements, and feature updates. The team reviews the current state of event support and assigns tasks to work with GTM teams. They also discuss product announcements, focusing on features that have reached a level of maturity and are now exciting, despite being available for a while.
key_points: Speaker_00 mentions that event support needs to be nailed down and assigns tasks to work with GTM teams
The team discusses product announcements, considering features that have reached a level of maturity
Speaker_01 suggests using MAU as a metric to measure excitement levels for features
Speaker_02 mentions that having a full-fledged feature is more important than just releasing small updates
decisions: To work with GTM teams to assign event support
To focus on product announcements for features that have reached a level of maturity

discussion_topics.summary: The team discusses the current state of event support and assigns tasks to work with GTM teams
The team discusses product announcements, focusing on features that have reached a level of maturity and are now exciting
The team reviews feature updates, considering what features to highlight in product announcements

next_steps: To assign event support tasks to GTM teams
To finalize product announcements for the commit event
To review and stack rank features for product announcements
